Album Notes
Additional personnel: Cowboy Jack Clement, Steve Wariner.
On his 2005 debut, MY KIND OF MUSIC, deep-voiced country crooner Ray Scott melds his tales of rural restlessness with slick, pop-inspired production. Some songs offer a rock-tinged, ZZ Top-like energy, but the album&#039;s crowning achievement is the title track, which nods to numerous country legends and features Scott dumping a woman because she&#039;s never heard of Kris Kristofferson--as noble a reason for a break-up as a country tune has ever offered .
